    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="541"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Fox</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 14. The perfection of arrangements desired by the minister for foreign
                    affairs is now dependent upon his broad-minded conciliatory action, equally with
                    similar action on the part of the Government of Peru. You will not fail to make
                    clear that the mediating Governments can not doubt that their hope is well
                    founded; that the Governments of Peru and Ecuador will find in this protocol so
                    nice a balance of justice and so scrupulous a regard for the interests of both
                    Governments as to constitute a happy solution of the difficulties at present
                    existing between the two countries.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Lima for corresponding action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
